CS 640 Assignment 4 - TCPend

Group Members:
- Nathan Kurtz, nkurtz
- Quincy Sorrentino, sorrentino

Files:
- src/TCPend.java: argument parsing and mode selection
- src/Sender.java: sender side handshake, sliding window send, retransmission, fast retransmit, and close
- src/Receiver.java: receiver side handshake, buffering, cumulative ACKs, file output, and close
- src/Segment.java: packet encode/decode for the custom UDP payload format
- src/ChecksumUtil.java: one's complement checksum implementation
- src/TimeoutEstimator.java: RTT/timeout estimator from the assignment spec
- src/ConnectionState.java: sender connection bookkeeping
- src/Stats.java: end of run statistics
- src/Logger.java: required per segment logging format

Build:
- make

Run receiver:
- java -cp src TCPend -p <port> -m <mtu> -c <sws> -f <file name>

Run sender:
- java -cp src TCPend -p <port> -s <remote IP> -a <remote port> -f <file name> -m <mtu> -c <sws>

Notes:
- Keep MTU at or below 1430 
- Data packets after the initial handshake are sent with the ACK flag set.
- This implementation uses cumulative ACKs, timeout based retransmission, and fast retransmit on 3 duplicate ACKs.
